<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-08-27T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-08-27T13:00:00-05:00" n="360" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d360">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">693.003/758: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Delegation at the Chinese Tariff
                                    Conference</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-08-27T14:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">August 27,
                                        1926—2 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>41. With reference to Conference 57 August 7, 3 p.m. and 59, August 27, 3
                                p.m.,<note n="55" xml:id="d360fn55">Latter not printed.</note> you
                            may inform Arnold that he has been designated as American delegate to
                            Tariff Revision Commission at Shanghai. Department is informed that
                            Arnold has received instructions from Department of Commerce in this
                            regard.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>